nodes.text: Nes Ukul was a male padawan of the Jedi Order. He sacrificed himself on a planet which he did not know the name of, defending a species whose language he could not speak. Ukul's master later commented that the padawan's sacrifice was noble. The antiques dealer Antron Bach later remembered Ukul's sacrifice when considering if he should give his own life to allow the Corellian Resistance member Miru Nadrinakar to escape the Galactic Empire.
Nes Ukul was first mentioned in "The End of History" a short story written by Alexander Freed and published in Star Wars Insider 154. The story did not include Ukul's species.
